file=Product/price/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: price-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — 1 dedicated script + inherits from Shared OS (2026-07-15)\nassigned_agent: price (Product / Pricing & Packaging)\ndate_added: 2026-07-10\ndate_filled: 2026-07-15\n · p:=All logical scripts live in `Shared OS/logical/` (§13.5). Price owns 1 dedicated script for pricing methods and inherits cross-agent scripts. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| # \| Script \| Source Book 1 \| Book 1 URL \| Source Book 2 \| Book 2 URL \| Route \| · tb=\|---\|--------\|--------------\|------------\|---------------\|------------\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| `pricing_methods.py` \| Nagle, *The Strategy and Tactics of Pricing* (3rd Ed., 2002, Routledge) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/strategytacticso0000nagl) — FREE \| Van Westendorp, *"NSS Price Sensitivity Meter"* (1976) — public domain \| Widely documented methodology \| B/C \| · tb=\| Script \| Source Book \| Book URL \| Why Price Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|------------\|----------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `experiment_methods.py` \| Kohavi et al. + OpenStax \| [experimentguide.com](https://experimentguide.com/) / [openstax.org](https://openstax.org/) \| Power analysis, guardrails for revenue experiments \| · tb=\| `signal_detection.py` \| OpenStax Statistics 2e (2023) \| [openstax.org](https://openstax.org/) — FREE \| WTP survey significance and CI \| · tb=\| `investor_metrics.py` \| Croll & Yoskovitz + Skok \| Commercial + free \| LTV:CAC, revenue guardrails \| · tb=\| `capital_budgeting.py` \| Brealey & Myers (12th Ed., 2017) \| Commercial \| NPV/WACC for pricing investment analysis \| · tb=\| `decision_analysis.py` \| Clemen & Reilly (2012) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/) \| Conjoint design selection, sensitivity analysis \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| wtp_methods (Van Westendorp, conjoint — conventions) \| ✅ Cleared \| `pricing_methods.py` (van_westendorp, conjoint_part_worth, conjoint_wtp) \| · tb=\| revenue guardrail thresholds \| ✅ Cleared \| `pricing_methods.py` (Gabor-Granger optimal price, value_based_pricing_range) + `investor_metrics.py` (LTV:CAC) \| · tb=\| value-metric selection heuristics \| ✅ Cleared \| `pricing_methods.py` (value_based_pricing_range) \| · tb=\| grandfathering-default reasoning \| ✅ Cleared \| `pricing_methods.py` (Nagle Ch.13 — pricing ethics framework) \| · sm:=- **pricing-research** → imports `pricing_methods.py` (van_westendorp, conjoint, Gabor-Granger) + `signal_detection.py` (survey significance)\n- **packaging-tiers** → imports `pricing_methods.py` (conjoint_part_worth for feature→tier mapping)\n- **pricing-experiment-discipline** → imports `experiment_methods.py` (MDE, power, guardrails, SRM) + `pricing_methods.py` (price_elasticity)\n- **price-change-governance** → imports `pricing_methods.py` (value_based_pricing_range for fair-pricing check)\n